<dl id="un1032em"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1032">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1032em"> (NLI.3) 32(em)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> paly:</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It will be observed that the description of the field is first set down, the blazoner giving its plain tincture or describing it as burely, party, <mark>paly</mark> or barry, as powdered or sown with roses, crosslets or fleurs-de-lys. <small> &ldquo;HERALDRY&rdquo; <a name="EBHY" href="/udra/udex.htm#EBHY"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911), p. 328/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07269f" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07269f">VI.C.07:269(f)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
